refsect1.para:
The <smin; tool minimises the state space in the SVC format in &infile;
using bisimulation reduction and saves the result to &outfile;. The SVC file
must have been generated by &lpe2lts;.

Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.


    &opt_h;
    &opt_help;



        display help message and terminate





    &opt_version;



        display version information and terminate





    &opt_q;
    &opt_quiet;



        do not display warning messages





    &opt_v;
    &opt_verbose;



        display concise intermediate messages





    &opt_s;
    &opt_strong;



        minimise using strong bisimulation (default)





    &opt_b;
    &opt_branching;



        minimise using branching bisimulation





    &opt_a;
    &opt_add;



        do not save the minimised state space but a copy of the original state
	space with an extra state parameter indicating the (branching)
	bisimulation class a state belongs to





    &opt_t;
    &opt_tau;



        specify an action that should be considered to be a tau
